                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/6–2744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-27T13:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 27, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>460. In view of fact that Department’s 386 June 24 arrived after subordinate
                    members of Financial Mission had submitted their resignations to Millspaugh and
                    at urgent behest of Millspaugh, Black and Pixley to whom the message was shown,
                    I have not delivered the Department’s message to other members of the mission.
                    These three men all believe that mission’s present improved position might be
                    seriously compromised by splitting its ranks at present time when unanimity of
                    action is highly desirable if mission is to remain as a useful and efficient
                    unit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
